## Overview

Proprietary solutions currently provide the ability to make a booking with limited capability to Cancel or Reschedule that booking from within the actual booking workflow. 

None of the existing proprietary solutions support cancellations / rescheduling after the call has ended. 

The intention is for a national solution to support the full range of workflow actions expected from a booking system. This includes the ability to cancel and ammend and existing booking.

The key challenge to overcome is how to support appropriate cancelling and rebooking for patients regardless of which service they have contacted. In order to acheieve this, a single national registry of bookings is required. This will allow any service with the correct authority to potentially remove or rebook a booking made for the patient.
